The paper discusses the design issues and challenges related to the secure 5G mobile backhaul architecture, which involves networking, security, and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also focuses on the security aspect of the mobile backhaul, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses various issues related to information theory and communication technologies, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of Software Defined Networking and millimeter Wave technologies, which could place it in cs.COM (Computer Networks and Communications) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
